# Basic HTTP Requests
# Demonstrates GET, POST, PUT, PATCH, DELETE with headers and bodies.
# All examples use httpbin.org — a free HTTP testing service.

### Simple GET
GET https://httpbin.org/get

### GET with headers
GET https://httpbin.org/headers
Accept: application/json
X-Custom-Header: hello-from-zed

### POST with JSON body
POST https://httpbin.org/post
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Ada Lovelace",
  "email": "ada@example.com",
  "role": "engineer"
}

### PUT — replace a resource
PUT https://httpbin.org/put
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "id": 1,
  "name": "Ada Lovelace",
  "email": "ada@example.com",
  "role": "lead engineer"
}

### PATCH — partial update
PATCH https://httpbin.org/patch
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "role": "principal engineer"
}

### DELETE a resource
DELETE https://httpbin.org/delete

### POST form data
POST https://httpbin.org/post
Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded

username=ada&password=secret123

### GET with query parameters
GET https://httpbin.org/response-headers?X-Custom=zed-rest-client&Version=1.0

### HEAD request — headers only, no body
HEAD https://httpbin.org/get

### OPTIONS — check allowed methods
OPTIONS https://httpbin.org/get

### GET with authentication
GET https://httpbin.org/bearer
Authorization: Bearer my-secret-token

### Basic auth
GET https://httpbin.org/basic-auth/user/passwd
Authorization: Basic dXNlcjpwYXNzd2Q=
